    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[Ke60] Kesten, Harry, Uniform distribution {${\\rm mod}\\,1$}. Ann. of Math. (2) (1960), 445--471.",
      "remarks": "Kesten \\cite{Ke60} proved that if\\[f(\\alpha,\\beta,n)=\\frac{1}{\\log n}\\sum_{1\\leq k\\leq n}(\\tfrac{1}{2}-\\{\\beta+\\alpha k\\})\\]then $f(\\alpha,\\beta,n)$ has asymptotic distribution function\\[g(c)=\\frac{1}{\\pi}\\int_{-\\infty}^{\\rho c}\\frac{1}{1+t^2}\\mathrm{d}t,\\]where $\\rho>0$ is an explicit constant."
    },
